Spinach Artichoke Chicken Bake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless chicken breast'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'cloves garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh basil,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1 (', 'unit': '14.6 ounce) can', 'name': 'artichoke hearts in water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes,'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'seasoned bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Heat olive oil and butter together in a large, ovenproof skillet over medium heat.. When butter is sizzling, add chicken pieces. Season with salt and pepper. Brown one side of the chicken pieces, 3 to 5 minutes; turn, and add diced red onion, minced garlic, and minced fresh basil. (See Note.). Cook, stirring often, until garlic is fragrant and onion is softened, about 3 minutes. Season with pepper flakes, and add artichokes and tomatoes. Stir in spinach; remove skillet from heat.. Combine Italian seasoned bread crumbs and shredded Parmesan cheese. Sprinkle bread crumb mixture over skillet contents.. Bake in the center of the preheated oven, uncovered, until bubbly and brown, about 25 minutes. Garnish with fresh basil and serve warm.

name: Sweet Potato and Bacon Pizza
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 2/3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dry yeast'}, {'quantity': '4 1/3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'sweet potato'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'rosemary'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Parmigiano Reggiano cheese'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'fontina cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Parmigiano Reggiano cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'jalapeno peppers,'}
steps: For dough, mix yeast and water and let stand for 10 minutes. Add flour and salt, and stir with a wooden spoon for 2 minutes to form a soft, sticky dough. Scrape down sides of bowl, cover, and let rise in a cool spot until doubled in size, 8 to 12 hours.. Use a wet hand to deflate and de-gas the dough, and form into a ball. Cover and store in the refrigerator until needed.. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Pierce sweet potatoes with a knife and place on a baking sheet.. Roast in the preheated oven until soft, about 1 hour. Let cool until cool enough to handle, about 10 minutes.. Scoop sweet potato flesh into a bowl—you will need about 2 1/2 cups. Add salt, black pepper, cayenne, olive oil, rosemary, lemon zest, and lemon juice, and mash until smooth. Stir in Parmigiano Reggiano, and taste for seasoning. Set aside.. Preheat the oven to 450 degrees F (235 degrees C).. Add bacon to a cold, dry, nonstick skillet. Place over medium-high heat, and cook, separating bacon pieces with tongs, until almost crisp, 7 to 10 minutes. Transfer to a plate lined with paper towels; set aside.. To assemble pizza, pour olive oil on a sheet pan and spread over evenly; place on dough, and use oiled hands to press out to the edges. If dough is very elastic, let dough rest and relax for a few minutes, then continue to stretch. Repeat this process as needed to stretch dough to cover the pan.. Dollop sweet potato mixture onto dough; Spread a thin layer over crust with the back of a spoon. Top evenly with mozzarella, bacon, fontina, and jalapenos. Finish with another dusting of Parmigiano Reggiano.. Bake in the preheated oven until crust is golden, and cheese is browned, 30 to 35 minutes. Remove from oven; cool in the pan for 5 to 10 minutes. Transfer to a board and slice with a pizza cutter.

name: Boursin Chicken Pot Pie
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'leek, white and pale green parts, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'button mushrooms, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'reduced-sodium chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5.3-ounce)', 'name': 'semi-soft cheese with garlic and fine herbs (siuch as Boursin®)'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen mixed vegetables'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': '(14.1-ounce) package', 'name': 'rolled refrigerated unbaked pie crust'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat. Add leek and mushrooms. Cook and stir until tender and any liquid has evaporated, about 5 minutes.. Whisk together broth, Boursin®, sour cream, and mustard in a bowl. Add to the skillet. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly, about 2 minutes.. Add frozen mixed vegetables and cook 3 minutes more. Stir in chicken and return to a simmer, about 1 minute.. Transfer hot filling to a 9-inch pie plate or 10-inch quiche dish.. Cut 3 slits in the center of the pie crust. Gently fold pie crust in quarters. Unfold pie crust atop the hot filling. Press edges of pastry to the inside edge of the pie plate, flute as desired.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden brown and bubbly, about 20 minutes. Let stand 15 minutes before serving.. Enjoy!

name: Philly Cheesesteak Smothered Tater Tots
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(2 pound)-package', 'name': 'tater tots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(12 ounce) box', 'name': 'frozen sandwich beef'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Worcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Montreal steak seasoning'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a large baking sheet with foil; arrange tater tots on the sheet in a single layer.. Bake in the preheated oven until golden, about 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, cook and stir onion, green pepper, and red  pepper in a large skillet over medium-high heat for 5 minutes. Add beef, Worcestershire sauce, and steak seasoning. Cook until most of liquid has evaporated, about 6 minutes.. Divide beef mixture over baked tater tots with a slotted spoon. Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top.. Bake until cheese is melted and beginning to brown, about 5 minutes more.

name: Olive Cheese Balls
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sharp Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, softened'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '36', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'pimiento-stuffed green olives'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'ranch dressing for serving'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': 'cracked black', 'name': 'cracked black'}
steps: Combine cheese and butter in a food processor and process until mixed together. Add flour, paprika, and cayenne. Process just until dough comes together. Turn out dough and shape into a disc. Chill, covered, until slightly firm and easy to handle, about 30 minutes.. Meanwhile, drain liquid from olives and spread out on paper towels to dry.(The olives should be completely dry before wrapping with dough.). Line a 10x15-inch rimmed baking sheet with parchment paper. Pinch off a piece of dough about the size of a walnut half. Flatten and wrap around an olive, enclosing completely. Roll to make a smooth ball. Place on the prepared baking sheet. Repeat with remaining dough and olives, spacing olive balls about 1 1/2 inches apart. Freeze until firm, at least 1 hour (and up to 1 month).. Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Bake frozen cheese balls until lightly browned and dough is set, 15 to 18 minutes. Let cool 5 minutes. Serve with ranch and garnish with pepper.

name: Quick-Pickled Carrots and Radishes
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'carrots, peeled and cut into thin sticks'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'radishes, trimmed and sliced'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sea salt'}
steps: Put vegetables in 2 (1-quart) screw-top jars (carrots in one; radishes in the other).. Combine vinegar, water, sugar, and salt in a medium saucepan; bring to a simmer over medium heat, stirring to dissolve salt and sugar. Remove from heat and pour over vegetables in the jars, pressing down to fully submerge (each jar should get about half the liquid). Screw on lids and shake to combine. Chill, covered, for at least 4 hours (and up to 3 weeks).

name: Crustless Ricotta Quiche
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ricotta cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole milk'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'freshly grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped fresh basil, plus leaves for garnish'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'arugula'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes, halved'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'balsamic vinegar for serving'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 9-inch pie dish.. Whisk together eggs, ricotta, and milk in a bowl. Stir in Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic, salt, and pepper; pour into the prepared dish.. Bake in the preheated oven until puffed and golden on the edges and a toothpick inserted into center comes out clean, about 25 minutes. Let stand for 15 minutes.. Meanwhile, toss together arugula, tomatoes, and oil in a medium bowl. Just before serving, top quiche with arugula mixture. Cut into 4 slices. Garnish with additional basil and pepper and serve with vinegar.

name: Ham and Butternut Squash Spaghetti
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'smoked ham, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, thinly sliced'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'peeled, seeded, and diced butternut squash'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mascarpone cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped Italian flat leaf parsley'}, {'quantity': '14', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'spaghetti'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'finely grated Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese'}
steps: Heat olive oil over medium heat in a large skillet. Stir in ham and cook until the edges are slightly browned, about 3 minutes.. Stir in garlic; cook until fragrant and edges are barely golden, about 1 minute.. Pour chicken broth over ham and garlic; bring to a simmer. Stir in butternut squash, red pepper flakes, and salt. Cook until squash is tender, about 15 minutes. Stir in black pepper and reduce heat to low.. Gently stir mascarpone cheese into squash mixture until completely incorporated. Stir in Italian parsley. Remove from heat and cover.. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook spaghetti in the boiling water, stirring occasionally until cooked through but firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Drain and return to pot.. Pour butternut-mascarpone sauce over spaghetti, stirring until combined. Sprinkle Parmigiano-Reggiano cheese over spaghetti and serve.

name: Loaded Broccoli Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'broccoli florets'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon, coarsely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10-ounce) can', 'name': 'condensed cream of chicken soup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '30', 'unit': None, 'name': 'crackers, coarsely crushed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly coat a 2-quart baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.. Cook broccoli in a large pot of boiling, lightly salted water for 1 minute; drain. Rinse with cold water; drain again and set aside.. Cook bacon in a large skillet over medium until crisp. Using a slotted spoon, remove bacon to a paper towel lined plate. Crumble bacon when cool.. Add onion to the skillet with bacon drippings; cook over medium about 5 minutes or until tender.. Meanwhile, combine soup , sour cream, garlic powder, salt, and pepper in a large bowl.. Add broccoli, bacon, and cooked onions to the soup mixture and stir to combine. Add cheese, stir.. Transfer broccoli mixture to prepared baking dish.. Combine crushed crackers and melted butter in a small bowl. Sprinkle crumb mixture over casserole.. Bake 45 minutes or until bubbly and golden.. Serve hot and enjoy!

Garnish with smoked paprika and parsley.

Add cranberries, jalapeno, pickled jalapeno, brine, red onion, and sugar into a food processor and pulse until very finely chopped.. Combine cranberry mixture with softened cream cheese and asiago cheese and stir until well blended. Refrigerate until ready to serve.

name: Cheesy Mashed Sweet Potatoes

Discard sage. Add Parmesan, half-and-half, salt, and pepper. Mash with a potato masher until smooth.. Heat oil in a small skillet over medium heat. Toast pecans, panko, and chopped sage, stirring frequently, about 3 minutes. Sprinkle mixture over sweet potato mixture. Garnish with additional sage leaves.

name: Beet Pickled Deviled Eggs
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'beets'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar, or as needed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'peppercorns'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'hard boiled eggs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'dash', 'name': 'hot sauce'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'radish slices'}
steps: For brine, drain beet juice into a small saucepan; set beet slices aside. Add the 1/2 cup vinegar, sugar, salt, and peppercorns, and bring to a low boil over medium heat, stirring until sugar dissolves, 3 to 5 minutes. Let cool completely, about 20 minutes.. Place eggs in a jar or glass bowl just large enough that brine will completely cover eggs; pour in brine. Top up with vinegar as needed to cover eggs completely. Refrigerate, covered, for at least 12 and up to 24 hours. The longer eggs are in brine, the deeper pink they will be.. Slice eggs in half lengthwise from top to bottom with a sharp knife. Remove yolks and place in a bowl. Mash yolks with a fork until smooth, and stir in mayonnaise, Dijon, the 1 teaspoon vinegar, and hot sauce; season with salt and pepper. As an option, if you have a small food processor, place all filling ingredients in it, and blend until smooth.. Spoon filling evenly into egg whites or add mixture to a piping bag or resealable plastic bag with one corner clipped. Pipe mixture into egg white halves, garnish as desired, and serve.

name: Pappardelle with Jammy Onion Ragu
ingredients: {'quantity': '7', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, divided'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'yellow onions'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'low-sodium chicken broth or vegetable broth'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'bay leaves'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fresh thyme, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oil-packed sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'dried pappardelle'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'shaved Parmesan cheese, for serving'}
steps: Melt 5 tablespoons butter in a very large, deep, heavy-bottomed skillet or an 8-quart Dutch oven over medium heat. Add onions and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Toss to coat in butter. Cook, covered, stirring occasionally, until onions are tender, about 15 minutes. Increase heat to high. Cook, stirring constantly, until onions start to brown, 3 to 5 minutes.. Reduce heat to medium and add garlic; cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute. Add tomato paste. Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture begins to darken, 1 to 2 minutes. Add wine to skillet, then use a wooden spoon or spatula to scrape up any browned bits from bottom of pot. Simmer for 2 minutes.. Add broth, bay leaves, thyme, crushed red pepper, and cloves. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, until liquid is reduced and onions are jammy, with just a bit of liquid at the edges of skillet, about 25 minutes.. While sauce simmers, cook pasta according to package directions. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup cooking water. Remove sauce from heat.. Remove  and discard bay leaves. Stir in sun-dried tomatoes, vinegar, black pepper, and remaining 2 tabelspoons butter and 1/2 teaspoon salt. Stir cooked pasta into warm sauce, adding reserved pasta cooking water a little at a time until sauce is desired thickness. Serve with Parmesan cheese and garnish with thyme.

name: Tex-Mex Ground Beef and Potato Skillet
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'hash brown potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'corn kernels'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'zucchini'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'beef broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(10 ounce) can', 'name': 'diced tomatoes and green chilies, (such as Ro-Tel® Original)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'taco seasoning, mild or hot'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions, sliced'}
steps: Heat a large skillet over medium heat. Cook and stir ground beef, breaking up the pieces as it cooks, until browned and crumbly. 3 to 5 minutes. Drain off excess fat.. Add potatoes, corn, zucchini, beef broth, RO-TEL, taco seasoning, and cumin. Season with salt and pepper. Bring to a boil, cover, reduce heat, and simmer until vegetables are tender, 20 to 25 minutes. Taste and adjust seasonings.. Stir in Cheddar, and allow to melt. Remove from heat. Garnish with dollops of sour cream and sliced green onions, and serve immediately.

name: Roasted Red Pepper Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red bell peppers'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon, juiced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'cloves garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'fresh basil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'prepared horseradish'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}
steps: Preheat a grill for medium heat and lightly oil the grate. Cut peppers in half. Remove and discard stems, seeds, and membranes.. Place peppers, skin side up, on the preheated grill, directly over heat; cook until slightly charred, 3 to 5 minutes. Turn peppers over and char the other side. Remove from the grill to cool slightly.. Combine peppers, mayonnaise, lemon juice, garlic, horseradish, and smoked paprika in the container of a blender; cover and blend until smooth.

name: Spring Roll Bowl
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'vermicelli noodles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'large shrimp -'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'butterhead lettuce, torn into bite-sized pieces'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'carrots, peeled and julienned'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'nglish cucumber, julienned'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado, sliced'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions, sliced on a bias'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'mint leaves (or torn large leaves)'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'salted peanuts'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'creamy peanut butter'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light coconut milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'hoisin sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'roasted peanuts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sambal oelek (optional)'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'rice vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fish sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ginger'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'birds eye chile, thinly sliced (optional)'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Cook vermicelli noodles according to package directions. Run under cold water to cool. Divide noodles among four bowls.. Add one fourth of the cooked shrimp to each bowl. On the side of the noodles arrange 1 cup of lettuce, 1/4  cup carrots, 1/4  cup cucumber, and 1/4  an avocado to each bowl.. Meanwhile for Nam Chom combine rice vinegar, fish sauce, lime juice, ginger, and birds eye chile (optional) in a small bowl.. For the peanut sauce combine peanut butter, coconut milk, hoisin sauce, lime juice, peanuts and sambal oelec in a small bowl; whisk until smooth.. Top bowls with green onions, mint leaves and peanuts. Serve with peanut sauce and/or Nam Choc.

name: Italian-Style Green Bean and Artichoke Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(9 ounce) packages', 'name': 'frozen artichoke hearts'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': '(28 ounce) cans', 'name': 'green beans'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'chopped parsley for garnish'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Lightly grease a 9x13-inch baking dish.. Combine Italian bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, garlic, salt, and pepper  in a large bowl. Reserve 1/3 cup breadcrumb mixture and set aside.. Add artichokes, green beans, and 1/2 cup olive oil to the bowl and gently fold to combine well. Pour mixture into the prepared baking dish and sprinkle with reserved breadcrumb mixture. Drizzle with remaining olive oil; cover with foil.. Bake in the preheated oven until heated through, about 30 minutes. Uncover and bake until lightly golden and bubbly around the edges, 10 to 15 minutes more. Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

name: Boursin Chicken, Mushroom, and Asparagus Skillet
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/2 to 2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'chicken tenders'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shallots'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'herbes de Provence'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken stock'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'asparagus pieces'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5.2 ounce) package', 'name': 'Boursin® Shallot and Chive Cheese, roughly chopped'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh snipped chives for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Pat chicken tenders dry with paper towels, and season all sides with salt and pepper.. Melt butter with olive oil in a large, nonstick skillet over medium heat. When butter is sizzling, add chicken tenders and cook until browned, 2 to 3 minutes per side. Remove to a plate and keep warm.. Add shallots to the same skillet, and stir for about 30 seconds, then add mushrooms. Stir until mushrooms begin to soften, about 2 minutes. Add garlic and herbes de Provence and cook, stirring, about 30 seconds.. Stir in chicken stock and wine. Add asparagus and another pinch of salt.. Place chicken tenders on top of vegetables, and add any accumulated juices. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and cook until chicken is no longer pink at the center and juices run clear, about 5 minutes. An instant-read thermometer, inserted near the center, should reach 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Turn off heat, add Boursin, and stir until melted. Garnish with chives, if desired, and serve warm.

name: Tres Leches Mashed Potatoes
ingredients: {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'russet potatoes ('}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'evaporated milk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'buttermilk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': '1 tablespoon', 'name': 'chives, or to taste'}

name: Creamy Sage and Garlic Pork Chops
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'bone-in', 'name': 'rib pork chops'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sage'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '15', 'unit': None, 'name': 'sage leaves'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth or stock'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}
steps: Pat chops dry with paper towels and season both sides with salt, and pepper. Sprinkle both sides of chops with 1 teaspoon rubbed sage, and set aside.. Heat olive oil and butter in a large skillet over medium heat until sizzling. Add sage leaves in a single layer and cook about 2 minutes. Turn and continue cooking until the leaves are crispy, about 2 more minutes. Remove to a paper towel to drain, then chop.. Add seasoned chops to the same skillet and brown both sides, 3 to 5 minutes per side. Remove chops to a plate.. Add minced garlic to the skillet and cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Stir in flour and cook, stirring, until all flour is moistened with the oil and begins to bubble. Add chicken broth and stir rapidly until smooth, 1 to 2 minutes. Pour in white wine and cook, stirring, 1 to 2 minutes. Stir in remaining 1/2 teaspoon rubbed sage.. Gradually stir in cream, and simmer until sauce thickens, about 2 minutes. Return chops to the skillet, and cook in the sauce for an additional 3 to 5 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the center of chops should read 145 degrees F (63 degrees C).. Sprinkle with chopped fried sage leaves and serve immediately.

name: Walking Takis Street Corn
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'ears corn'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': '(1 ounce) bags', 'name': 'flavored rolled tortilla chips, such as Takis®'}
steps: Heat an outdoor grill over medium-high heat. Grill corn 8 minutes. Flip and grill 8 minutes more. Remove from heat and place on a cutting board.. Whisk mayonnaise, sour cream, Parmesan, cilantro, and black pepper together in a large bowl.. Remove husks from the cob and discard. Cut corn kernels from the cob; stir into mayonnaise mixture.. Open bags of Takis, and divide corn mixture between the bags. Top with extra Parmesan and cilantro if desired. The Takis are your dipping tool. No forks required.

name: Air Fryer Baked Yams
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'yam'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Scrub yam clean and dry with a paper towel. Rub all over with olive oil.. Place yam in the preheated air fryer, and cook until tender when pierced with a fork, 15 to 20 minutes.

name: Marry Me Bean Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, pressed'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'great northern beans'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tomato sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'spinach'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'basil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Melt butter in a Dutch oven. Add onions and cook until soft and translucent, 5 to 6 minutes.. Add garlic, red pepper, and paprika; cook and stir until garlic is fragrant, about 1 minute.. Add beans, and cook until simmering, about 5 minutes. Mash half of the beans.. Stir in chicken broth, sun-dried tomatoes, and tomato sauce. Add heavy cream and Parmesan cheese, and stir until well combined.. Add spinach and basil and cook until spinach is wilted. Season with salt and pepper.

name: Ramen Omelet with Spinach, Mushrooms, and Cheese
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 ounce) package', 'name': 'ramen, seasoning packets discarded'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, divided'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'splash', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Bring 2 cups of water to a boil in a saucepan; add ramen and cook until tender, about 3 minutes. Drain and set aside.. Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a skillet. Add mushrooms; cook and stir until tender, about 5 minutes. Add spinach and cook until wilted, stirring constantly, about 2 minutes. Remove from skillet and set aside.. Mix eggs with splash of milk in a bowl. Melt remaining 1 tablespoon butter in the same skillet. Add eggs, top with half of the ramen, 1/2 of the mushroom-spinach mixture, and 1/4 cup cheese. Season with salt and pepper. Once eggs are set, fold omelet in half and top with remaining mushroom mixture and remaining cheese.

name: Mixed Vegetable Curry
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ghee or clarified butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '1/2 inch piece)', 'name': 'ginger,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'tomato'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'serrano pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'carrots'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green peas'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'russet potato'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground turmeric'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fenugreek seeds'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped cilantro, for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Heat ghee in a large, nonstick pan over medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring, until lightly brown, about 8 minutes. Add garlic and ginger and cook, stirring, until fragrant, about 1 minute.. Add tomato, serrano pepper, carrots, peas, potato, turmeric, coriander, cumin, fenugreek, chili powder, and salt, and cook, stirring, for about 5 minutes.. Reduce heat to low, cover, and let vegetables steam in their own juices until potatoes are fork tender, about 25 minutes. Stir about halfway through cooking time, and make sure the pan isn't too dry. If vegetables are sticking, add 1 or 2 tablespoons water, replace the lid, and continue cooking. Taste; season with salt.. Garnish with chopped cilantro. Serve warm, with naan, or similar flatbread.

name: Spicy Creamy Cucumber Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'English', 'name': 'cucumbers'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'plain Greek yogurt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'hot sauce (such as Tabasco'}
steps: Place sliced cucumbers into a large bowl.. Whisk Greek yogurt, lime juice, Thai chili sauce, ketchup, and hot sauce together in a small bowl until smooth; stir into sliced cucumbers. Refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.

name: Avocado Caprese Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mozzarella balls, or "pearls," drained'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'avocado -'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh basil leaves, or to taste, plus more for garnish (optional)'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Combine mozzarella, halved cherry tomatoes, and chopped avocado in a small bowl. Tear basil leaves into pieces and sprinkle over the other ingredients.. Drizzle on balsamic vinegar and extra virgin olive oil and toss to combine. Season with salt and pepper.. Divide into two serving bowls and garnish with additional fresh basil. Serve immediately.

name: Mississippi Mud Potatoes
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'diced potatoes'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onions'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C). Spray an 8x8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray. Set aside.. Combine potatoes, cheese, bacon, onion, mayonnaise, garlic, salt, and pepper in a large bowl. Transfer to the prepared dish.. Bake until potatoes are fork tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Top with green onions.

name: Sheet Pan Summer Gnocchi
ingredients: {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'gnocchi'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'zucchini'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'summer squash'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'onion,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pint', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'tomato basil chicken sausage'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'Italian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'pesto'}
steps: Heat oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Place gnocchi, zucchini, summer squash, onion, tomatoes, and sausage on a rimmed sheet pan. Drizzle olive oil evenly over mixture. Add garlic and Italian seasoning; toss to coat.. Bake in the preheated oven until vegetables are tender, about 35 minutes. Dollop pesto over the mixture, toss to combine, and serve immediately.

name: Cheesy Zucchini Rice
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) can', 'name': 'low-sodium chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'long grain rice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded unpeeled zucchini'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Bring broth to a boil in a saucepan; stir in rice. Cover, reduce heat to low, and cook until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed, 20 to 25 minutes.. Remove from heat. Stir in melted butter. Add zucchini and cheese. Stir, cover and let sit until cheese is melted, about 10 minutes. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

name: Mini Chicken Pot Pies
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 count) packag', 'name': 'frozen mini pie shells'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'pie crust'}, {'quantity': '1 3/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'frozen mixed vegetables'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5.3-ounce) package', 'name': 'soft French cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1 3/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'water'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a sheet pan with parchment paper, and place individual pie shells on the sheet. Allow refrigerated pie crust to come to room temperature on the counter, about 15 minutes.. Place frozen vegetables into a microwave-safe dish, add water, cover, and microwave on High until hot, about 5 minutes. Drain.. Stir Boursin into vegetables until melted. Stir in cream, chicken, and black pepper; season with salt. Distribute mixture evenly among pie shells.. Using a 3-inch round biscuit cutter, cut 8 circles from refrigerated pie crust. Place a circle on top of each pie and crimp edges together. Using a sharp knife, cut two slits in the form of an "X" in the center of each top crust. Stir egg and water together in a cup until well combined; brush each pie lightly with egg wash.. Bake in the center of the preheated oven until lightly browned, about 20 to 25 minutes, or until lightly browned. Remove to cool on a rack about 10 minutes.. Remove foil tins from pies and serve warm.

name: Corn with Tarragon and Lime
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14.4 ounce) package', 'name': 'corn'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter, cubed'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh tarragon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'lime, zested'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}
steps: Empty frozen corn into a 2-quart saucepan, and stir in water. Bring to a boil over medium-high heat, cover, and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, about 4 minutes. Drain well.. Return saucepan to the stove over low heat, add butter, tarragon, lime zest, and juice. Stir until butter has melted and corn is warm, about 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper, and serve.

name: Ramen Vegetable Stir Fry
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'low-sodium soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'ramen noodles (2 packages), flavor packets disgarded'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red pepper'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'broccoli florets'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sugar snap peas'}
steps: Combine soy sauce, lime juice, Thai chili sauce, maple syrup, ginger, and red pepper flakes in a small bowl. Stir until smooth; set aside.. Bring 4 cups of water to a boil in a pot. Discard flavor packet. Add ramen noodles to boiling water; cook until noodles are tender, 4 to 5 minutes. Drain noodles and set aside.. Heat sesame oil in a skillet over medium-high heat. Add garlic, onions, red peppers, broccoli, and sugar snap peas, and cook and stir until softened, about 5 minutes. Reduce heat to low; stir in sauce, and cook until thickened, about 3 minutes. Add in ramen noodles and serve warm.

name: Boursin Chicken Baked Ziti
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecorino Romano cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'breadcrumbs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'ziti pasta'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried Italian herb seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cooked chicken'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(5.2 ounce) package', 'name': 'soft French cheese, such as Boursin® Garlic and Fine Herbs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C) and grease an 8x8-inch baking dish.. Combine grated pecorino and breadcrumbs in a small bowl; set aside.. Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil. Add ziti, and cook until tender with a bite, about 11 minutes. Drain; reserve about 2 tablespoons pasta water.. Meanwhile, melt butter in a large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add chopped onion; cook and stir until onion begins to soften, 2 to 3 minutes. Stir in garlic, herb seasoning, and red pepper flakes, and cook about 30 seconds.. Turn off heat. Stir in chicken, spinach, cream, Boursin, and mozzarella, stirring until cheeses are melted and ingredients are well combined.. Stir drained ziti into chicken mixture. Loosen the sauce with reserved pasta water, if needed. Pour chicken and sauce mixture into the prepared baking dish. Sprinkle pecorino and bread crumb mixture over the top.. Bake in the center of the preheated oven until bubbly and lightly browned, 20 to 30 minutes. Serve warm.

name: Tuscan Chicken Casserole
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'boneless chicken breasts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'talian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(4 ounce) can', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, pressed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chicken bouillon granules,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chicken broth'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'oil'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Spray an 8x8-inch baking dish with nonstick cooking spray.. Season both sides of chicken with Italian seasoning, paprika, onion powder, pepper flakes, garlic powder, salt and pepper. Place in the prepared pan. Place spinach over chicken, mushrooms over spinach, and sun-dried tomatoes over mushrooms. Top with mozzarella and Parmesan cheese.. For sauce, beat cream, Parmesan cheese, garlic, cream cheese, chicken bouillon, chicken broth, and oil together in a bowl until just combined. Season with salt and pepper. Pour mixture over chicken.. Bake casserole in the preheated oven until bubbly, chicken is no longer pink, and juices run clear, 20 to 25 minutes.  An instant-read thermometer inserted in the center of chicken should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).

name: Shrimp Ramen Stir Fry
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oyster sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'rice vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili crisp,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'grapeseed oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sesame oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'broccoli florets'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'carrots'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'shrimp'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(3 ounce) package', 'name': 'ramen noodles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'sesame seeds'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions for garnish'}
steps: For sauce, add soy sauce, oyster sauce, sesame oil, rice vinegar, chili crisp, and garlic to a small bowl. Heat grapeseed oil in a small saucepan. Carefully pour heated oil into the bowl; set sauce aside.. Heat remaining 1 teaspoon sesame oil in a wok or heavy skillet. Add broccoli, carrots, bell pepper, and onion. Sauté until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 3 minutes. Add garlic and stir until fragrant, about 35 seconds. Pour in sauce, and add shrimp. Cook for approximately 2 minutes.. Meanwhile, open ramen package; discard seasoning packet. Bring 2½ cups water to a boil in a small saucepan. Add noodles and cook for 2 minutes. Drain; stir noodles into the wok; toss to coat. Garnish with black and white sesame seeds, and chopped green onion.

name: Mediterranean Baked Fish
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic,'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cherry tomatoes,'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'dried Italian herb seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olives'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh spinach'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy cream'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'fish fillets'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooked rice or pasta (optional)'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh parsley for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in an oven-safe nonstick skillet over medium heat. When oil shimmers, add onions and cook, stirring frequently, until onions are translucent, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in garlic, and cook, stirring, about 30 seconds.. Add cherry tomatoes and wine, and season with salt and pepper. Add 1 teaspoon Italian seasoning and red pepper flakes. Toss to combine, and cook about 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in sliced olives, chopped spinach, and cream.. Nestle fillets into vegetable mixture, sprinkle each fillet with salt and pepper, and drizzle remaining olive oil over the entire dish. Brush the olive oil to cover the surface of each fillet. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 teaspoon Italian seasoning.. Bake in the preheated oven until fish flakes easily with a fork, 20 to 25 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the center should read 145 degrees F (63 degrees C).. Serve with hot, cooked pasta or rice, and garnish with fresh parsley.

name: Caramelized Onion Pasta
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'onions'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chili onion crunch'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'spaghetti'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': '2 tablespoons grated Parmesan cheese,'}
steps: Heat olive oil and 1 tablespoon butter in a large skillet over medium-low heat. Stir in onions until well coated. Cook, stirring occasionally, until they start to caramelize and turn golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes. You can add water, 1 tablespoon at a time, as onion mixture cooks to speed up caramelization and keep onions moist.. Add garlic and cook until fragrant, about 1 minute. Stir in sun-dried tomatoes, soy sauce, chili onion crunch, and season with salt and pepper.. Meanwhile, bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook spaghetti in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Drain, reserving 1/2 cup pasta water.. Transfer pasta to the skillet with caramelized onions. Toss everything together until well coated, and stir in remaining tablespoon of butter. Add reserved pasta water, if needed, a tablespoon at a time.. Garnish with chopped parsley and Parmesan cheese, and serve.

name: Sausage Stuffed Mini Peppers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'hot Italian sausage'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onions'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '5.3-ounce) package', 'name': 'herb flavored Gournay cheese (Such as Boursin'}, {'quantity': '9', 'unit': None, 'name': 'mini bell peppers'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh parsley sprigs or fresh basil for garnish'}
steps: Crumble sausage into a nonstick skillet over medium heat; cook and stir for 2 to 3 minutes.. Add mushrooms, red pepper flakes, and green onions, reserving about 3 tablespoons of green onion tops. Stir until sausage is browned, 3 to 4 more minutes. Drain any excess fat.. Remove skillet from heat and stir in Boursin until melted and well blended with the other ingredients.. Fill each pepper half with about 1 1/2 tablespoons sausage mixture; place filled peppers on a baking sheet.. Preheat the oven’s broiler.. Broil until filling is lightly browned, about 3 minutes. Place on a serving tray and sprinkle with reserved green onion tops. Garnish with sprigs of fresh parsley or fresh basil. Serve warm or at room temperature.

name: Apple Pecan and Bacon Salad with Maple Vinaigrette
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'apple pie spice'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'strips', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red delicious apple'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'ranny Smith apple'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'mixed spring salad greens'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pecans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'havarti cheese'}
steps: For vinaigrette, add vinegar, maple syrup, olive oil, salt, pepper, and apple pie seasoning to a glass jar with a tight-fitting lid; cover and shake to combine.. Place bacon in a large skillet and cook over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until evenly browned, about 10 minutes. Drain bacon slices on paper towels.. Combine mixed greens with red delicious apple, Granny Smith apple, and onion in a large bowl. Top with pecans and havarti cheese. Drizzle with vinaigrette and serve immediately.

name: Smoked Pork Chops with Sauerkraut
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooked pork chops'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(16 ounce) jar', 'name': 'sauerkraut'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'apple'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'beef broth'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'bacon grease'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'clove garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': None, 'name': 'juniper berries'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'bay leaf'}
steps: Melt butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Quickly sear meat for 2 minutes on each side, and remove from pan. Reduce heat to medium, add onions, and saute for 3 minutes.. Stir in sauerkraut, apple, beef broth, bacon grease, garlic, juniper berries, and bay leaf. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 20 minutes.. Remove bay leaf, add chops back to skillet, and nestle in the kraut. Simmer just until chops are warmed up, 3 to 5 minutes. Cooking further will dry them out.

name: Pumpkin Tiramisu Bundt Cake
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'cake flour'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground nutmeg'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cloves'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground allspice'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'pumpkin puree'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mascarpone cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'espresso powder'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'coffee liqueur'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mascarpone'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "confectioner's sugar"}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'whole milk'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cocoa powder'}
steps: Preheat oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Grease a 10-cup Bundt pan with a baking spray containing flour.. Sift together cake flour, baking powder, cinnamon, salt, baking soda, ginger, nutmeg, cloves, and allspice.. Beat butter, white sugar, and brown sugar together in a large bowl until light and fluffy, about 3 minutes. Add in eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each addition, then turn mixer to medium-high and beat batter for an additional 3 minutes. Add in pumpkin, mascarpone, whole milk, and vanilla, and beat until completely incorporated. Add in half the dry ingredients and mix until just combined. Add in remaining dry ingredients and mix until just combined.. Pour batter evenly into the prepared pan. Tap pan sharply on the counter several times to remove any larger air bubbles.. Bake in the preheated oven until a bamboo skewer inserted into the center of the cake comes out clean, 65 to 75 minutes. Cool cake in pan for 5 minutes.. Meanwhile, for espresso syrup, stir hot water, espresso powder, sugar, and coffee liqueur together until completely combined and dissolved.. Use a bamboo skewer to poke several holes all over the bottom of the cake, only going about 3/4 of the way into the cake. Gradually drizzle espresso syrup over cake, letting it soak in slightly before adding more. It will seem like a lot of liquid, but it will all soak in. Continue to cool cake in the pan for 20 minutes more, then carefully invert onto a serving platter to cool completely.. For icing, whisk together mascarpone, confectioner’s sugar, whole milk, vanilla, and salt until smooth and combined. Drizzle icing over cooled cake. Sift cocoa powder over icing before it sets. Serve cake at room temp for best flavor and texture, but store any extra in the refrigerator.

name: Italian Steak Pizzaiola
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'ribeye steaks'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon freshly ground black', 'name': 'freshly ground black'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil, divied'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white or red wine'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': None, 'name': 'roma tomatoes, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'tomato paste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olives'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chopped parsley'}
steps: Season steaks with 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.  Heat 1 tablespoon oil in a large deep skillet over high heat. Add steaks to skillet and cook, undisturbed, until browned about 2 minutes.  Flip and cook 1 more minute. Remove steaks from skillet and set aside.. Add remaining oil to skillet and turn heat to medium.  Add onions, remaining salt and pepper, and cook, stirring occasionally until softened.  Add garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add wine and scrape bottom of skillet to loosen any browned bits. Add tomatoes  and oregano and bring mixture to a simmer.  Simmer until tomatoes soften, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.. Use a potato masher or the back of a spoon to crush the tomatoes.  Add in tomato paste and olives and stir to combine.  Simmer for 2 minutes.. Return steaks and any juices accumulated to the skillet and cover the steaks in the tomato mixture.  Cook until the steak is heated through, 2 to 3 minutes.  Remove from heat and add parsley. Serve with crusty bread or over pasta or rice.

name: Marinated Fall Vegetable Pasta Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red wine vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'shallot, finely minced'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '16', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'button mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'carrots'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'cauliflower'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(7.5 ounce) jar', 'name': 'marinated artichoke hearts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'bowtie pasta'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'bunch', 'name': 'kale'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8.5 ounce) jar', 'name': 'sun-dried tomatoes in olive oil'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley'}
steps: Whisk vinegar, brown sugar, Dijon mustard, shallot, salt, garlic powder, black pepper, red pepper, and oregano together in a large bowl. Drizzle in olive oil and whisk until well combined. Add mushrooms, carrots, cauliflower, and artichoke hearts to the dressing and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour and preferably overnight.. For salad, bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook bow-tie pasta at a boil, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Drain and set aside to cool.. Massage kale to soften it slightly and add it to the marinated vegetables. Add in sun-dried tomatoes, smoked mozzarella, and parsley, and toss to coat. Taste; season with salt and pepper.

name: Southwestern Sweet Potato and Black Bean Pasta Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'pasta, such as penne or bow-tie'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chipotles'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cumin'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'red wine vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'sweet potatoes'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon freshly', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce)', 'name': 'can black beans, drained and rinsed'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup minced', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped cilantro'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cotija cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook pasta at a boil, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 12 minutes. Drain and set aside to cool.. For vinaigrette, place 2 chipotle peppers, plus 1 tablespoon sauce into a blender. Add garlic, oregano, honey, and red wine vinegar, and blend on high until well combined. Drizzle in the 2/3 cup olive oil with blender running until smooth, and set aside. Chop remaining peppers finely and stir into vinaigrette. Refrigerate until ready to use.. Toss potatoes in 2 tablespoons olive oil, black pepper, and remaining salt. Coat a baking sheet with nonstick spray or line with parchment, and spread potatoes in an even layer on the sheet.. Roast in the preheated oven until browned, about 20 minutes, stirring halfway through. Remove from oven and set aside.. In a large bowl combine cooked pasta with black beans, onion, cilantro, and toss.  Add in potatoes and 3/4 cup vinaigrette, or more as needed, and toss gently (reserve any remaining vinaigrette for another use). Season with salt and pepper, and stir in cotija cheese. Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.

name: Fall Harvest Orzo Pasta Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'butternut squash'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '1/4 cup plus 2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fresh thyme'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'orzo pasta'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'apple cider vinegar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'mustard'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'Brussels sprouts'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'walnuts'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'dried cranberries'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'feta cheese (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Line a rimmed baking sheet with foil or parchment; place bacon on the sheet.. Bake bacon in the preheated oven until crisp, about 10 minutes. Remove bacon from tray and drain on paper towels. Reserve drippings in the pan.. Increase the oven temperature 425 degrees F (220 degrees C).. Add butternut squash, onion, 2 tablespoons oil, 1 teaspoon salt, 1/2  teaspoon pepper, and thyme to the pan with bacon drippings and toss to coat.. Roast squash in the preheated oven until browned, about 20 minutes. Set aside.. Meanwhile, bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil. Cook orzo in the boiling water, stirring occasionally, until tender yet firm to the bite, about 10 minutes. Drain and set aside to cool.. For vinaigrette, add vinegar, maple syrup, mustard, garlic powder, remaining salt, and remaining pepper into a bowl. Whisk in remaining 1/4 cup olive oil until well combined. Set aside.. Add pasta, Brussels sprouts, walnuts, cranberries, and vinaigrette to a large bowl and toss to combine. Gently stir in cooked vegetables and bacon. Serve immediately or refrigerate until ready to serve.

name: Sheet Pan Tomato Soup
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'plum tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'small', 'name': 'sweet onion'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'garlic cloves'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'heavy whipping cream'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'basil leaves'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'light brown sugar'}

name: Cucumber Feta Quinoa Salad
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'quinoa'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'English cucumber'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'red pepper,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(2.25 ounce) can', 'name': 'black olives,'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red onion'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'feta crumbles'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'red wine vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'garlic clove,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'fresh oregano'}
steps: Bring water and quinoa to a boil in a saucepan. Reduce heat to medium-low, cover, and simmer until quinoa is tender, 15 to 20 minutes. Drain, and cool to room temperature, about 20 minutes.. Combine quinoa, cucumber, red peppers, olives, and red onion in a large bowl; sprinkle with feta cheese.. Whisk olive oil, vinegar, garlic, mustard, parsley, and oregano together in a small bowl. Pour dressing over salad, toss well to combine, and serve.

name: Parmesan Pesto Roasted Cauliflower
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'head', 'name': 'cauliflower'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground pepper to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pesto'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 425 degrees F (220 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. In a large bowl, toss the cauliflower florets with olive oil, salt, and pepper until evenly coated. Spread cauliflower evenly in a single layer on the prepared baking sheet. Set the bowl aside.. Roast in the preheated oven until golden and crispy on the edges, 25 to 30 minutes, turning halfway through cooking time.. Transfer hot cauliflower back to the bowl and toss with pesto and Parmesan cheese. Serve immediately.

name: Stuffed Mini Peppers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'mini peppers,'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'whipped cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'everything bagel seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green onion, chopped'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Place peppers on a large baking sheet.. Combine cream cheese, Cheddar, everything seasoning, and green onion in a bowl. Mix well until evenly combined. Using a butter knife, spread each pepper with an equal amount of cheese mixture.. Bake in the preheated oven for 15 minutes. Turn the oven’s broiler to High and broil until cheese is browned on top, about 2 minutes.

name: French Onion Burgers
ingredients: {'quantity': '6', 'unit': None, 'name': 'hamburger buns'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onions'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'ground beef'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(1 ounce) packet', 'name': 'onion soup mix'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'havarti cheese'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}
steps: Preheat a large skillet over medium heat. Place hamburger bun halves, cut-sides down, in the hot skillet until lightly toasted, 2 to 3 minutes. Remove toasted buns to a plate.. Preheat an outdoor grill for medium heat. Heat butter in a large saucepan over medium heat on the grill. Add mushrooms and onions; season with salt and black pepper and cook and stir until mushrooms are lightly browned, about 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, mix ground beef and onion soup mix in a bowl using your hands. Form mixture into 6 hamburger patties.. Lightly oil grill grates. Grill burgers for about 5 minutes, then flip and grill to your desired doneness. A meat thermometer inserted near the center of patties should read 180 degrees F (82 degrees C).. Remove burgers from heat to rest for 5 minutes. Spread each bun with 1 tablespoon mayonnaise, and add burgers; divide mushrooms and onions between burgers to serve.

name: Classic Swiss Steak
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'round or rump steak'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'green bell pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'carrots'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'sliced mushrooms'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '(14.5 ounce) cans', 'name': 'stewed tomatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'fresh parsley'}
steps: Stir flour, kosher salt, black pepper, paprika, and garlic powder together in a small bowl. Pound steak with a meat mallet. Sprinkle meat with flour mixture on both sides and use the meat mallet to pound the mixture into the meat.. Heat oil in a large deep skillet or Dutch oven over medium-high heat until slightly shimmering.  Add meat and cook, undisturbed, until browned and releases easily from the pan, about 3 minutes. Flip steak and cook for 2 more minutes. Remove from the pan and set aside.. Add onion, bell pepper, carrots and mushrooms to the drippings in pan; cook and stir until onion is translucent, about 5 minutes. Stir in stewed tomatoes. Return steak to pan, along with any accumulated juices and bring to a simmer.. Cover, reduce heat and simmer until steak is tender, about 1 1/2 hours. Sprinkle with parsley and serve steak and tomato mixture over rice.

name: Southwestern Twice Baked Sweet Potatoes
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'sweet potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chipotle peppers in adobo'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'green onion'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '2 3/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'pepper Jack cheese,'}
steps: Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with foil or parchment. Rub potatoes evenly with oil and sprinkle evenly with 1 1/2 teaspoons salt. Pierce potatoes with a fork and place them on the prepared sheet.. Bake in the preheated oven until completely tender, 35 to 40 minutes.. Meanwhile, place bacon in a large skillet and cook over medium-high heat, turning occasionally, until crisp, about 10 minutes. Reserve 1 tablespoon bacon grease. Drain bacon on paper towels, chop, and set aside.. Cut the top 1/4 off the top of each potato and scoop out most of the potato, reserving intact skins with flesh about 1/8-inch-thick.. Add scooped flesh to a bowl with butter, reserved bacon grease, and remaining salt, and mash until creamy and only small lumps remain. Stir in chipotles and adobo sauce, maple syrup, green onions, sour cream, and 1 cup cheese. Divide filling evenly among potatoes and top each with 1 tablespoon cheese. Return potatoes to the lined baking sheet.. Return to the oven and bake until hot and cheese is melted, about 15 minutes.
